Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and finely dice @carrots{6%ounce}(peeled and finely diced). Finely dice @celery{2.5%ounce}(finely diced). Halve, peel, and dice half the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced half the onion). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced).

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium ovenproof pan{} over medium heat. Add chicken in a single layer; season with a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned all over, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in step 5).

Transfer chicken to a #plate{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add carrots, celery, and diced onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until veggies are softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> Lower heat if veggies begin to brown too quickly.

Add garlic and half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings); cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add 2 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon} to pan with veggies. Once melted, stir in @flour{2%tablespoon}; cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add 1¼ cups water, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil and cook until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat.

> If filling is too thick, stir in another splash of water.

Stir in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} until melted, then stir in chicken. Season with salt and pepper.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer filling to an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} after stirring in chicken.

Place 1 TBSP butter in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Remove @Pillsbury™ Buttermilk Southern Homestyle Biscuits{6%ounce} from package; peel apart each biscuit at the center to create two thinner biscuits.

> For a crispier topping, cut the biscuits into quarters instead of peeling them apart.

Evenly top chicken filling with biscuits, then brush with melted butter.

Bake on top rack until biscuits are golden brown and chicken is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Let pot pie cool at least ~{5%minutes} before serving. Spoon into shallow #bowls{} or #plates{} and serve.